o-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 17, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zpe1665703174928.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zpe1665703174928.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zpe1665703174928.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zpe1665703174928\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Provide runtime information about the negotiated options of the current or previous connection.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__section_w3703ab1b5b1_w3704ab1b5_w3705ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d98081e49\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">SMTP security drivers</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__section_w3706ab1b5b3_w3707ab1b5_w3708ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d98081e58\">Expected Input</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__p_d132332e1_d132333e1_d132334e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">Properties</code>,\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">Parameters</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__p_d132335e1_d132336e1_d132337e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">OutBuf</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">OutBufLen</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__p_d132338e1_d132339e1_d132340e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">DrvArea</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__section_w3709ab1b5b5_w3710ab1b5_w3711ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d98081e85\">Expected Output</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__p_d132344e1_d132345e1_d132346e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">OutDataLen</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">ErrMsg</code>,\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">ErrMsgLen</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__p_d132347e1_d132348e1_d132349e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">DrvArea</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__section_w3712ab1b5b7_w3713ab1b5_w3714ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d98081e107\">Return Status</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__p_d132353e1_d132354e1_d132355e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_SUCCESS</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__section_w3715ab1b5b9_w3716ab1b5_w3717ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d98081e118\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__p_d132359e1_d132360e1_d132361e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_RTINFO</code> function should be\n        implemented in security drivers that negotiate options with the SMTP mail server. It must\n        provide the result of those negotiations in <code class=\"ph codeph\">OutBuf</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__p_d132362e1_d132363e1_d132364e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_RTINFO</code> function is called\n        when the <code class=\"ph codeph\">GetSecurity</code> operation of the UPOPMAIL component is called. The\n        driver specifies whether it supports this function code in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_DRVINFO</code>\n        call.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__p_d132365e1_d132366e1_d132367e1\">The function should return the negotiated options from\n        the currently established connection or the last one that was used. If no connection has\n        ever been established, it can return zero in <code class=\"ph codeph\">OutDataLen</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__p_d132368e1_d132369e1_d132370e1\">The runtime information must be supplied in the form\n        of a Uniface list of name-value pairs, separated by a byte whose value is 27\n            (<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"name=value<var class=\"keyword varname\">[27]</var>name=value\"</code>). You can use the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">PutItem</code> utility function to assemble this list, writing it to\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">OutBuf</code>. The length of the list should not exceed\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">OutBufLen</code>. The actual length must be provided in\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">OutDataLen</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpe1665703174928__p_d132371e1_d132372e1_d132373e1\">This function code must return success.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534546\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534546\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "USEC_RTINFO Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 17, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Provide runtime information about the negotiated options of the current or previous connection. Use SMTP security drivers Expected Input Properties , Parameters OutBuf , OutBufLen DrvArea Expected Output OutDataLen , ErrMsg , ErrMsgLen DrvArea Return Status USEC_SUCCESS Description The USEC_RTINFO function should be implemented in security drivers that negotiate options with the SMTP mail server. It must provide the result of those negotiations in OutBuf . The USEC_RTINFO function is called when the GetSecurity operation of the UPOPMAIL component is called. The driver specifies whether it supports this function code in the USEC_DRVINFO call. The function should return the negotiated options from the currently established connection or the last one that was used. If no connection has ever been established, it can return zero in OutDataLen . The runtime information must be supplied in the form of a Uniface list of name-value pairs, separated by a byte whose value is 27 ( \"name=value [27] name=value\" ). You can use the PutItem utility function to assemble this list, writing it to OutBuf . The length of the list should not exceed OutBufLen . The actual length must be provided in OutDataLen . This function code must return success. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}